# MongoDB Expert Plugin Configuration

This file contains your local MongoDB connection settings. The values in this file
will be used by the plugin when connecting to your database.

## Configuration Options

### connectionUri
MongoDB connection string. Examples:
- Local: mongodb://localhost:27017
- With auth: mongodb://user:pass@localhost:27017
- Atlas: mongodb+srv://cluster.example.com/
- SRV: mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.xxxxx.mongodb.net/

### defaultDatabase
The default database to use when no database is specified.

### timeout
Connection timeout in milliseconds (default: 30000).

### debugMode
Enable debug logging (true/false).

## Security Note

This file may contain sensitive credentials. Add it to your .gitignore:

```
.claude/*.local.md
```
